The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 8: Wasteful expenditure of public money will be subject to courts scrutiny, the Supreme Court said today in a message directed at the Mayavati governments statue-installing spree.          
	We may even ask your (Uttar Pradesh) government to place your budget before us. Taxpayers money cannot be spent arbitrarily. You cannot spend it whichever way you like, a two-judge bench told the states counsel and Mayavati confidant Satish Mishra.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Three hoax calls claiming that bombs have been placed at four prominent buildings, including two government hospitals, created panic in Delhi this morning.                   
	 Dharamsala (PTI): An MA student of a government college has been booked for ragging in Dharamsala, Himachal Pradesh. This is the first ragging case in the state after an anti- ragging law came into force. Manoj Thakur was booked after the college complained he had ragged a first-year student.                                                                                                                           
